Yes it is but you can close the issue....
I found my mistake. I used a union type as argument -> thus the DI does of course not know what the real dependency is. (Just changed to PHP8.0 and tried to get around, I thought it might be a good idea to use `Interface|RealObject` as an argument since I always pass the first argument by myself.

```PHP
public function example(Interface|SpecificClass $class){

}

// ....
$myClass = new SpecificClass();
Yii::$container->resolveCallableDependencies([$this, 'example'], [$myClass])
```
will always throw the error but this is my fault.

However, a better error like
```PHP
if($class instanceof ReflectionUnionType){
    throw new Exception('Union types cannot be handled via DI`)
}
```
would be awesome in that case

Sorry for the late response, I wasn't on my PC the last days (was on vacation)
Since the new branch php81 doesn't seem to exist anymore I tried it with the master and the issue still remains.
This is my basic example/test code (my `User` class implements `\yii\web\IdentityInterface`
```PHP
public function example(IdentityInterface|User $user): string
{
    return $user->email;
}

public function actionTestDi()
{
    $user = new User();
    $user->email = 'test@test.com';
    $email = \Yii::$container->resolveCallableDependencies([$this, 'example'], [$user]);
    echo "<pre>";
    var_dump($email);
    echo "</pre>";
    die();
}
```
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6122122/149765300-ca6711af-476a-4ba2-aded-73d599dc5e58.png)
https://github.com/yiisoft/yii2/blob/master/framework/di/Container.php#L668
 `$param->getType()` returns an object of type `ReflectionUnionType` and this one doesn't seem to have an `isBuiltin` function.
Maybe I missunderstood something?
